      <hedline>
        <hl1>To Keep the Mideast Talks Alive</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mazdak Atighi letter says tenacious American belief in power of secular political process to overcome ancient animosities is only cause for hope that Middle East may have future different from its past</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Both Sides Take Steps to Achieve Calm in Mideast'' (front page, Oct. 19):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Both Sides Take Steps to Achieve Calm in Mideast'' (front page, Oct. 19):</p>
        <p>If the Palestinians are being killed for throwing rocks, why do they continue to throw them? Why are Palestinians so ready to die and not try to find a peaceful way to share and respect Jerusalem? It appears they want it all or nothing, with no compromise. How can you find peace with people who don't value their own lives?</p>
        <p>MOSHE KATZ  Kew Gardens, Queens, Oct. 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
